g compiler loop in the background, these demos will break live on stage.\n\n### 4. Connections\nThese assumptions form a domino cascade. If Analyst C\u2019s **\"The paste input is high-friction\" (Assumption 1)** is correct, builders will try to solve it by creating native integrations (e.g., WhatsApp bots, Chrome Extensions). However, building these pipelines immediately triggers my own **\"Permissionless Clipboard\" (Assumption 3)** vulnerability: platform API restrictions and enterprise security policies will block the data flow. Solving the UI bottleneck directly activates the security bottleneck, killing the product's viability."
