ations:\n\n1. **State Gap Mapper** \u2014 strongest fit across all four equally weighted judging criteria, with an obvious \u201cmissing transition\u201d reveal.\n2. **Five Second Mirror** \u2014 safest polished-demo option and the clearest 30-second transformation.\n3. **First Wrong Turn** \u2014 highest educational upside if restricted to typed, verifiable algebra.\n\n## 3. Potential Counterarguments\n\nOQL has the strongest viral, multi-user product story; reframing its output as an editable \u201cbest next question\u201d would reduce risk, but also weaken its defining promise. State Gap Mapper could appear like a diagram generator unless missing transitions produce evidence-linked test cases and genuinely interactive editing."
