work far beyond a three-day build.\n\n4. **Assumption: A compelling one-shot demo predicts sustained user value.**  \n   **Why It\u2019s Hidden:** The ideas are optimized for judge-visible \u201caha\u201d moments: chaos enters, clarity appears. That rewards immediate legibility more than repeated use or measurable behavior change.  \n   **What If It\u2019s Wrong:** Concepts such as \u201cComplexity Dial,\u201d \u201cFuture Self Receipt,\u201d and \u201cFive Second Mirror\u201d may win attention but lack retention. The better product may be less theatrical and more deeply embedded in an existing workflow.\n\n5. **Assumption: Users will trust AI to collapse ambiguity into one answer.**  \n   **Why It\u2019s Hidden:** Decisiveness is framed as relief from cognitive load.  \n   **What If It\u2019s Wrong:** \u201cOne Question Left\u201d\u2014arguably the most promising idea\u2014loses its advantage. Users may dispute omitted preferences or resist algorithmic compromise, requiring visible evidence, uncertainty, corrections, and appeal mechanisms.",
