ot \"which assumptions invalidate the most promising ideas?\" but: **\"Which idea pairs its aha with (a) a persistent artifact the already-open ChatGPT tab can't replicate, (b) a verifiable ground truth, and (c) errors that are visible, cheap, and correctable?\"** Rank by survival through the human-fixed gates \u2014 friction-aversion, consent, error cost \u2014 since the judging process already over-weights demo legibility.\n\n## 5. Confidence\n**Medium-High.** High on the behavioral verdicts (cognitive friction, wrapper absorption) \u2014 they rest on market evidence, not speculation. Medium on coordination dynamics and error-cost severity \u2014 context-dependent, untested against real users. The funnel structure (access \u2192 signal \u2192 accuracy \u2192 acceptance \u2192 retention) is robust; the individual gate probabilities are not.",
