detector that fabricates is net-negative. Kimi's own field note \u2014 that only ideas 4 and 7 \"survive unscripted judge input\" \u2014 quietly concedes the other eight are fragile.\n\n## 3. Better Alternatives\n\n**Selection principle: only build tools whose output is verifiable against the input at a glance.** *Alt-Text Atelier* (judge sees the image), *Stack Trace Confessional* (deterministic input, checkable diff), and *Fine Print Flags* (flags anchored in the original clause) degrade gracefully under adversarial demos.\n\nStronger still: graft *Claim Evidence Receipt*'s one genuinely novel mechanic \u2014 claim-to-source linking \u2014 onto the coordination winner. **\"One Question Left\" with every extracted constraint hyperlinked to its exact chat line** converts silent failure into visible failure and is the only version with a real answer to the ChatGPT objection.",
