uld not be compressed.\n\nBoth also ignore benchmarkability. Without a labeled set of messy chats and human-agreed blockers, claims of reliability are anecdotal.\n\n## 4. New Angles\n\n- **Adversarial participants:** jokes, strategic ambiguity, changing preferences, edited transcripts, and participants gaming the extracted result.\n- **Failure recovery:** what happens when voters reject the premise of the generated question?\n- **Cold-start demo risk:** judges may paste a chat with no genuine decision, several blockers, or insufficient context.\n- **Success metric:** fewer messages may indicate resolution\u2014or merely disengagement and coerced consensus.",
