e Devil's Advocate's Charges Stand Unanswered\n\nFOR never addressed: manufactured consensus, verbose-participant bias (30 messages collapse to one question \u2014 *whose*?), sarcasm and silence-as-dissent, or consent for uploading friends' messages. The Devil's Advocate named One Question Left among \"the most fragile concepts.\" Silence on all four points.\n\n## 4. Reinforced Risk\n\nThe failure mode isn't a bad answer \u2014 it's **confident miscoordination**: the group votes on the wrong question, believes it's settled, and discovers otherwise at the airport. That is strictly worse than the paralysis it treats.\n\n**Closing note:** Even taken on its own terms, FOR is defending the *fragile* version. The only defensible build is my amended one \u2014 every extracted constraint hyperlinked to its source chat line \u2014 converting silent failure into visible failure. FOR has declined to adopt it. Vote AGAINST the proposal as stated.",
