gn \u2014 it was my fix.\n\n**4. Why AGAINST Wins**\nBoth FOR rounds were damage control adopting opposition fixes \u2014 the original proposal no longer exists on the table. What remains is a coin-flip demo riding on an unbenchmarked inference about social truth, dressed in virality. The question asked what collapses under real-world conditions. This does.\n\n**5. Confidence**\n**High** on the risk verdict \u2014 the verification gap survived every round unrebutted. Medium on contest outcome, since hackathons reward execution and a lucky demo can win. But the brief asked what fails in practice, not what might get lucky.",
